Summary: greenish-white fireball shoots horizontally from south to north for about one second
divs: Sighting DetailsMy sister and I had just gotten out of the car and were walking north up the driveway when I saw a greenish-white ball of light shoot across the horizon from south to north. It lasted about one second and then disappeared out of sight. I asked my sister if she just saw the shooting star and she said "Is that what that was?" I suppose it could have been a shooting star, but it was much larger in size than a shooting star and the vivid green color of it was unlike any shooting star I'd ever seen. Am wondering if anyone else in southeastern Wisconsin last night saw this? When I got in the house I immediately did a Google search on "report UFO" and came across this website and UFO Wisconsin, where I also filed a report.
